Synopsis:
   set status_notify [<text>]

Description:
   This variable sets the string displayed in the status bar when there is
   activity in a hidden window.  If the hidden windows have been inactive
   since the last time they were viewed, nothing is displayed.

   This string is represented as %F in the STATUS_FORMAT string.  It will
   expand to a list of active hidden windows when used in STATUS_NOTIFY.

Examples:
   Customizing the active window string in the status bar:
      /set status_notify Active: %F

See Also:
   set(4) status_format; window(4) notify_level

